data.meta_description:
1 likes, 0 comments - curiousernewyork on April 18, 2024: "NEW YORK | Jacqueline Kennedy Onassis Reservoir.

Today is rainy and cold. Just like NYC spring usually is - one day it’s 80s, another day it’s 60s. 

This place is one of my favorite places in Central Park. I used to live about 5-6 blocks from here and used to jog around this reservoir all year around. I just loved this place so much! It’s magical in all seasons! And now it’s extra magical because of the cherry blossoms! If you’re ever in NYC - come to this place!
